## Implementation Order
1. `index.html` (font)
2. `variables.css` (tokens — this breaks everything temporarily)
3. `global.css` (dark globals)
4. `Toolbar.module.css` + `Toolbar.jsx` (biggest visual payoff)
5. `Sidebar.module.css`
6. `PropertiesPanel.module.css`
7. `InputField.module.css`
8. `Modal.module.css`
9. `SvgCanvas.module.css`
10. `ThreePreviewPanel.module.css`
11. `App.module.css`

Steps 2-11 should be done in one pass to avoid intermediate broken state.

## What Does NOT Change
- Zero JS logic, event handlers, state management, or reducers
- Zero domain model / persistence changes
- Zero editor tool handler changes
- SVG icons in `ToolbarIcons.jsx` use `currentColor` — they auto-adapt to new theme
- Canvas drawing surface stays light
- All keyboard shortcuts, tool behaviors, clipboard operations unchanged

